---
import { SITE } from "@/consts";
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description={`Release notes`} contained>
  <article
    class="grid grid-cols-[minmax(0,1fr)] gap-10 max-w-(--reading-width)"
  >
    <header class="grid gap-[0.85rem]">
      <h1>{SITE.author}</h1>
      <p class="lede">Software <del>Stuff</del> Engineer</p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        Hi! I'm Thiago Moura. I'm a software engineer based in Belo Horizonte, Brazil. Most of my recent work has been related to platform engineering, product thinking, and practical AI.
      </p>

      <h2>Latest professional experiences</h2>
      <p>
        Over the last few years, I've worked on Cloud-native applications, product-critical platform capabilities, and internal AI tools meant to support engineering and product teams in their work. Some highlights include:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>
          Wrote Kubernetes operators and tooling to streamline development and operations workflows.
        </li>
        <li>
          Deployed and maintained Istio Service Mesh in production for a large retail environment, where operational clarity and resilience mattered.
        </li>
        <li>
          Worked on a custom API gateway built on top of Envoy Gateway, with an extensibility model that allowed users to write their own plugins in Java without fighting the platform.
        </li>
        <li>
          Led the design and implementation of an authorization server (on top of Keycloak) tailored to the emerging Chilean Open Finance ecosystem.
        </li>
        <li>
          Built an internal AI tool to help engineering teams understand how errors propagated through a complex microservices architecture.
        </li>
        <li>
          Built an internal AI tool to help product managers keep up with the evolution of Brazilian Open Finance regulation and understand its impact on the product roadmap.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How I work | Tenets</h2>

      <ul>
        <li>Critical thinking: always question assumptions and seek evidence.</li>
        <li>There is no silver bullet, and there is no free lunch. Fundamentals still rule, even in the AI era.</li>
        <li>Optimize when it matters. Not before, not after.</li>
        <li>Prevent accidental (or intentional) complexity. Simplicity pays off.</li>
        <li>Be an enabler: understand the product, stay empathetic, and help others move.</li>
        <li>Get close to the customer's pain points and fix them as they were your own.</li>
        <li>Abstract repetition and remove friction where it meaningfully improves the work.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
